  "description": [
    "GATHER TO PLEAD rnnTiirmm nnrn ruKintuiiLUKtn National Child Labor Committee Begins Convention at New Wiilard SMALL TOILERS CALLED NO LONGER ECONOMICAL Tragic Pictures Presented of Those Who Begin Work at Winter Dawn to Continue Eleven Honrs Tragic pictures of eight to ten year old children dragging their wan little todies to work in the mills of the United States at 530 oclock in the dawn of winter mornings there literally to earn their bread in the sweat Of their brows for eleven hours or more each day were presented at the opening sessions tnis morning ana anernoon of the eleventh annual conference on child labor under the ausp es of tlie national child labor committee in the large ballroom of the New Willard Hotel From all over the United States prominent men and women as well as workers in the ranks who have demoted their time and means to alleviating the sufferings of the mill children and other youthful laborers of the United States gathered at the New Willard to plan further campaigns in behalf of their charges and simultaneously across the street from the hotel at 1415 F street northwest LW J DR SAMUEL McCUXE LINDSAY Vice chairman national"
